'''<small>1,239,939</small>'''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2020 Republican primaries}}\n\n[[Category:2020 United States Republican presidential primaries by state|Florida Republican]]\n[[Category:2020 Florida elections|Republican primary]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{short description|Primary election in Florida, US}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2020 Florida Republican primary\n| country = Florida\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = No\n| previous_election = 2016 United States presidential election in Florida#Republican primary\n| previous_year = 2016\n| next_election = 2024 Florida Republican primary\n| next_year = 2024\n| election_date = March 17, 2020\n| votes_for_election = \n| party_name = \n| map_image = \n| map_size = \n| map_caption = \n| image1 = [[File:Donald Trump official portrait (cropped).jpg|x160px]]\n| candidate1 = [[Donald Trump]]\n| color1 = 283681\n| home_state1 = [[Florida]]<ref name=poloct31>{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/10/31/trump-florida-residence-063564|title=Trump, a symbol of New York, is officially a Floridian now|publisher=[[Politico]]|date=October 31, 2019|accessdate=February 3, 2020|url-status=live|author=Matthew Choi}}</ref>\n| popular_vote1 = '''1,162,984'''\n| percentage1 = '''93.79%'''\n| delegate_count1 = '''122'''\n}}\n[[File:Sample Ballot Republican Party Sumter County Florida.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A Republican Party sample ballot from [[Sumter County, Florida]].]]\n{{ElectionsFL}}\nThe '''2020 Florida Republican primary''' took place on March 17, 2020, as one of the three contests scheduled on that date in the [[Republican Party presidential primaries]] for the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 presidential election]].\n\n==Results==\nIncumbent United States [[President of the United States|president]] [[Donald Trump]] was challenged by three candidates: businessman and perennial candidate [[Rocky De La Fuente]] of [[California]], former congressman [[Joe Walsh (American politician)|Joe Walsh]] of [[Illinois]], and former governor [[Bill Weld]] of [[Massachusetts]]. Walsh withdrew from the race prior to the primary.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.miamiherald.com/news/politics-government/voters-guide/article240300096.html|title=Want to vote on whether Trump stays? First come the primaries. Here\u2019s what to know|author=Michelle Marchante|date=February 15, 2020|accessdate=February 15, 2020|work=[[Miami Herald]]}}</ref><section begin=\"FLresults\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right;\"\n|+ style=\"background-color:#f2f2f2;margin-bottom:-1px;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em 0.4em\" |2020 Florida Republican primary<ref name=\"FLDOE\">{{Cite web|url=https://results.elections.myflorida.com/downloadresults.asp?ElectionDate=3/17/2020&DATAMODE=|title=March 17, 2020 Primary Election|last=|first=|date=March 31, 2020|website=Florida Department of State|publisher=Florida Division of Elections|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Florida Republican Delegation 2020|url=https://www.thegreenpapers.com/P20/FL-R|publisher=The Green Papers|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Candidate\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | Votes\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" | %\n! Estimated<br>delegates\n|-{{party shading/Republican}}\n| '''{{sortname|Donald|Trump}}'''\n| '''1,162,984'''\n| '''93.79'''\n| '''122'''\n|-\n| {{sortname|Bill|Weld}}\n|39,319\n|3.17\n|\n|-\n| {{sortname|Joe|Walsh|Joe Walsh (American politician)}} <small>(withdrawn)</small>\n| 25,464\n| 2.05\n| \n|-\n| {{sortname|Rocky De La|Fuente}}\n| 12,172\n| 0.98\n|\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" | Total\n! 1,239,939\n! 100\n! 122\n|}<section end=\"FLresults\" />\n\n=== Results by county ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|+\n! colspan=\"10\" |<small>2020 Florida Republican primary</small>\n<small>(results per county)<ref n