{"title_page": "Kari Ukkonen", "text_new": "{{short description|Finnish football manager and former player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name= Kari Ukkonen\n| fullname = Kari Ukkonen\n| image =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1961|02|19}}\n| birth_place = [[Kuopio]], [[Finland]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.82|precision=0}}\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber =\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = 1979\u20131982\n| years2 = 1982\u20131986\n| years3 = 1986\u20131987\n| years4 = 1987\u20131991\n| years5 = 1991\u20131993\n| years6 = 1993\u20131996\n| clubs1 = [[Kuopion Palloseura|KuPS]]\n| clubs2 = [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]]\n| clubs3 = [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]]\n| clubs4 = [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]]\n| clubs5 = [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]]\n| clubs6 = [[LB Ch\u00e2teauroux|Ch\u00e2teauroux]]\n| caps1 =\n| caps2 = 107\n| caps3 = 32\n| caps4 = 38\n| caps5 = 39\n| caps6 = 52\n| goals1 =\n| goals2 = 16\n| goals3 = 8\n| goals4 = 3\n| goals5 = 1\n| goals6 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 1983\u20131996\n| nationalteam1 = [[Finland national football team|Finland]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 59\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n| manageryears1 =\n| manageryears2 = 2004\u20132006\n| managerclubs1 = [[Finland national football team|Finland]] ''(youth coach)''\n| managerclubs2 = [[Turun Palloseura|TPS]]\n}}\n'''Kari Ukkonen''' (born 19 February 1961 in [[Kuopio]]) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] former [[football (soccer)|football]] player and current football manager. As player, Ukkonen was fielded as [[defender (football)|defender]] as well as [[midfielder (soccer)|midfielder]].\n\nUkkonen represented Finland at the [[1980 Summer Olympics]] in [[Moscow]]. Three years later, he earned his first cap for [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in a 1\u20131 draw against Poland. The same year, Ukkonen was voted [[Finnish Footballer of the Year]] by sports journalists and the [[Football Association of Finland]].\n\nIn between, in 1982, Ukkonen had moved from Finland to [[Belgium]], when he was bought by [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]]. Ukkonen made his Belgian d\u00e9but on 13 November, when Cercle defeated [[K.S.V. Waregem|SV Waregem]] with 2\u20131. Ukkonen would go on to win the [[Belgian Cup]] with Cercle in 1985. Ukkonen would spend most of his career in Belgium, also playing for other [[Belgian League|First division]] teams as [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]], [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] and [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]]. Ukkonen ended his playing career with [[France|French]] side [[LB Ch\u00e2teauroux]]. He stayed in football as [[coach (sport)|manager]]. First he was coach of Finland's national youth team. He was [[head coach]] of Finland at the [[2001 FIFA World Youth Championship|2001 World Youth Championship]] in [[Argentina]]. His next job was manager of [[Turun Palloseura]].\n\n==Honours==\n*'''[[Belgian Cup]]:'''\n**'''Winner (4):''' 1985, 1988, 1989, 1992\n**'''Runner-up (1):''' 1986\n*'''[[Belgian First Division]]:'''\n**'''Winner (1):''' 1990-91\n**'''Runner-up (2):''' 1988\u201389, 1989\u201390\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.cerclemuseum.be Cerclemuseum.be] {{in lang|nl}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110706132844/http://www.antwerpsupporter.be/spelersarchief/spelersfiche.php?id=226 Kari Ukkonen player profile] {{in lang|nl}}\n*{{NFT player|pid=14246}}\n\n{{Finnish Footballer of the Year}}{{Turun Palloseura managers}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ukkonen, Kari}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Finnish football managers]]\n[[Category:People from Kuopio]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Finland]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cercle Brugge K.S.V. players]]\n[[Category:K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen players]]\n[[Category:R.S.C. Anderlecht players]]\n[[Category:Royal Antwerp F.C. players]]\n[[Category:LB Ch\u00e2teauroux players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Association football utility players]]\n[[Category:TPS Turku football managers]]\n[[Category:Mestaruussarja players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Finnish football manager and former player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name= Kari Ukkonen\n| fullname = Kari Ukkonen\n| image =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1961|02|19}}\n| birth_place = [[Kuopio]], [[Finland]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.82|precision=0}}\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber =\n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = 1979\u20131982\n| years2 = 1982\u20131986\n| years3 = 1986\u20131987\n| years4 = 1987\u20131991\n| years5 = 1991\u20131993\n| years6 = 1993\u20131996\n| clubs1 = [[Kuopion Palloseura|KuPS]]\n| clubs2 = [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]]\n| clubs3 = [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]]\n| clubs4 = [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]]\n| clubs5 = [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]]\n| clubs6 = [[LB Ch\u00e2teauroux|Ch\u00e2teauroux]]\n| caps1 =\n| caps2 = 107\n| caps3 = 32\n| caps4 = 38\n| caps5 = 39\n| caps6 = 52\n| goals1 =\n| goals2 = 16\n| goals3 = 8\n| goals4 = 3\n| goals5 = 1\n| goals6 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 1983\u20131996\n| nationalteam1 = [[Finland national football team|Finland]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 59\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n| manageryears1 =\n| manageryears2 = 2004\u20132006\n| managerclubs1 = [[Finland national football team|Finland]] ''(youth coach)''\n| managerclubs2 = [[Turun Palloseura|TPS]]\n}}\n'''Kari Ukkonen''' (born 19 February 1961 in [[Kuopio]]) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] former [[football (soccer)|football]] player and current football manager. As player, Ukkonen was fielded as [[defender (football)|defender]] as well as [[midfielder (soccer)|midfielder]].\n\nUkkonen represented Finland at the [[1980 Summer Olympics]] in [[Moscow]]. Three years later, he earned his first cap for [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in a 1-1 draw against Poland. The same year, Ukkonen was voted [[Finnish Footballer of the Year]] by sports journalists and the [[Football Association of Finland]].\n\nIn between, in 1982, Ukkonen had moved from Finland to [[Belgium]], when he was bought by [[Cercle Brugge K.S.V.|Cercle Brugge]]. Ukkonen made his Belgian d\u00e9but on 13 November, when Cercle defeated [[K.S.V. Waregem|SV Waregem]] with 2-1. Ukkonen would go on to win the [[Belgian Cup]] with Cercle in 1985. Ukkonen would spend most of his career in Belgium, also playing for other [[Belgian League|First division]] teams as [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]], [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] and [[Royal Antwerp F.C.|Royal Antwerp]]. Ukkonen ended his playing career with [[France|French]] side [[LB Ch\u00e2teauroux]]. He stayed in football as [[coach (sport)|manager]]. First he was coach of Finland's national youth team. He was [[head coach]] of Finland at the [[2001 FIFA World Youth Championship|2001 World Youth Championship]] in [[Argentina]]. His next job was manager of [[Turun Palloseura]].\n\n==Honours==\n*'''[[Belgian Cup]]:'''\n**'''Winner (4):''' 1985, 1988, 1989, 1992\n**'''Runner-up (1):''' 1986\n*'''[[Belgian First Division]]:'''\n**'''Winner (1):''' 1990-91\n**'''Runner-up (2):''' 1988\u201389, 1989\u201390\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.cerclemuseum.be Cerclemuseum.be] {{in lang|nl}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110706132844/http://www.antwerpsupporter.be/spelersarchief/spelersfiche.php?id=226 Kari Ukkonen player profile] {{in lang|nl}}\n*{{NFT player|pid=14246}}\n\n{{Finnish Footballer of the Year}}{{Turun Palloseura managers}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2011}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ukkonen, Kari}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Finnish footballers]]\n[[Category:Finland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Finnish football managers]]\n[[Category:People from Kuopio]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Finland]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Cercle Brugge K.S.V. players]]\n[[Category:K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen players]]\n[[Category:R.S.C. Anderlecht players]]\n[[Category:Royal Antwerp F.C. players]]\n[[Category:LB Ch\u00e2teauroux players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Association football utility players]]\n[[Category:TPS Turku football managers]]\n[[Category:Mestaruussarja players]]\n", "name_user": "Majavah", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up,typo(s) fixed: 1-1 \u2192 1\u20131, 2-1 \u2192 2\u20131", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kari_Ukkonen"}
